  "prompt": "Does Congress party digging their grave slowly as they are opposing everything done by PM Modi like saying Jay Shriram or surgical strikes?",
  "response": "It is important to approach any political analysis with nuance and objectivity. Political dynamics are complex and involve multiple factors. The Congress party, one of India's major political entities, has often positioned itself in opposition to the policies and actions of Prime Minister Narendra Modi's government, as is common in democratic systems where opposition parties scrutinize and challenge the ruling party's decisions.\n\nTheir opposition to various actions, such as the promotion of certain slogans or military actions, is a part of their political strategy and ideological standpoint. However, asserting that the Congress party is \"digging its grave\" solely based on their opposition is a simplified perspective. Political fortunes can change due to a wide range of influences, including public opinion, election strategies, grassroots mobilization, policy proposals, leadership dynamics, and current events.\n\nPublic response to the Congress party\u2019s opposition can vary widely; some may view it as holding the government accountable, while others may perceive it negatively. The impact of such opposition depends on various elements such as the effectiveness of their communication, the popularity of the incumbent government, and the socio-political context at any given time.\n\nUltimately, the success or failure of any political party in a democracy like India depends on a complex interplay of factors beyond just their stance on particular issues. Voter perception, electoral strategy, leadership, and pressing socio-economic challenges all collectively shape the political landscape.",
